# Cloudflare Pages _redirects. Copied verbatim from `frontend/public/` into
# `dist/` at build time by Vite's static-asset pass.
#
# Trailing-slash → non-trailing canonical. The build emits `dist/<slug>.html`
# (file, not directory) for every indexable route (see scripts/prerender.ts),
# so Pages serves `/<slug>` with 200 directly. Anyone who lands on `/<slug>/`
# — old inbound links, third-party share tools that auto-append `/` —
# gets a 308 to the canonical no-trailing form. Search Console previously
# flagged the (old) `/<slug>` → `/<slug>/` 308 chain as "page avec
# redirection", suppressing the indexable URL.
#
# 308 (not 301) preserves the request method on rewrite; matches the
# default Cloudflare Pages emits for the inverse rule.

/grille/             /grille             308
/grilles/            /grilles            308
/aide/               /aide               308
/mentions-legales/   /mentions-legales   308
/confidentialite/    /confidentialite    308
/privacy/            /privacy            308
/compte/             /compte             308
